<div class="container">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="hero">
    <h1>Paper Bitcoin vs. <span class="h1-real">Real Bitcoin</span></h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Every way of holding bitcoin is essentially a different asset.<br>
    Only one of them is the real bitcoin &mdash; the <em>physical</em> bitcoin the rest of this site describes.<br>
    This page examines how the variations compare.</p>
  </header>

  <!-- §A — What happened to gold -->
  <section class="section section-opening">
    <h2>What happened to gold</h2>
    <p>In 1933, Executive Order 6102 caught gold in both of its forms. Paper gold &mdash; the certificates and bank claims that most "gold ownership" had quietly become &mdash; was cancelled by memo: banks converted certificates to fiat on instruction, and the state seized the ledger without touching the metal. Physical gold was surrendered too &mdash; not because the state could find it, but because its use was compromised, and anyone caught still holding it faced prison and fines; defiance was impractical. <a href="/the-bitcoin-migration.html">The Bitcoin Migration</a> tells this history in full. This page is about the different ways to hold bitcoin today &mdash; and how to recognize, and where possible minimize, exposure to 6102-type risks.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- §A2 — The four quadrants -->
  <section class="section quadrant-section">
    <h2>The four quadrants</h2>
    <p class="quadrant-lede">Gold fell to 6102 in both its forms. Bitcoin can fall in only one &mdash; and that form is a choice.</p>

